SIMPLE: optional
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Optional
<hw>Op"tion*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Involving an
option; depending on the exercise of an option; left to one's discretion
or choice; allowed but not compulsory; <as>as, <ex>optional</ex>
studies; it is <ex>optional</ex> with you to go or stay.</as></def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>See <er>Elective</er>,
<pos>n.</pos></def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If to the former the movement was not <qex>optional</qex>, it was
the same that the latter chose when it was <qex>optional</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Palfrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Original writs are either <qex>optional</qex> or peremptory.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Optionally</ent>⟦br⟧
